.TH MERCURY 1 "2026" "Mercury 1.9.5" "HERMES Manual"
.SH NAME
mercury \- HF radio modem with ARQ and broadcast data links
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mercury
.RB [ \-i
.IR device ]
.RB [ \-o
.IR device ]
.RB [ \-x
.IR sound_system ]
.RB [ \-m
.IR mode_index ]
.RB [ \-p
.IR port ]
.RB [ \-b
.IR port ]
.RB [ \-R
.IR model ]
.RB [ \-A
.IR address ]
.RB [ \-S ]
.RB [ \-G ]
.RB [ options ]
.br
.B mercury
.RB [ \-l " | " \-z " | " \-K " | " \-h ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mercury
is the modem component of the HERMES (High-Frequency Emergency and Rural
Multimedia Exchange System) project.
It provides ARQ (Automatic Repeat reQuest) and broadcast data links over
HF radio using FreeDV OFDM waveforms with LDPC forward error correction.
.PP
The ARQ link implements a half-duplex stop-and-wait protocol with adaptive
gear-shifting between FreeDV modes (DATAC4, DATAC3, DATAC1) based on
measured channel SNR, providing per-direction mode selection and a
reliability ladder that steps down immediately on errors and steps up
after consecutive clean acknowledgements.
.PP
Mercury exposes a VARA-compatible TNC (Terminal Node Controller) TCP
interface, allowing existing amateur radio software such as UUCP, Winlink,
and Pat to connect without modification.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Audio options"
.TP
.BI \-i " device"
Radio capture (input) device identifier.
For ALSA, use a device string such as \(lqplughw:0,0\(rq.
For PulseAudio, WASAPI, or DirectSound, omit this option to use the system default.
.TP
.BI \-o " device"
Radio playback (output) device identifier.
Same format as
.BR \-i .
.TP
.BI \-x " sound_system"
Audio subsystem to use.
Valid values:
.BR alsa ,
.BR pulse ,
.BR dsound ,
.BR wasapi ,
.BR oss ,
.BR coreaudio ,
.BR aaudio ,
.BR shm .
Default is
.B alsa
on Linux and
.B dsound
on Windows.
.TP
.BI \-k " channel"
Capture input channel layout:
.BR left ,
.BR right ,
or
.BR stereo .
Default is
.BR left .
.TP
.B \-z
List all available sound cards for the selected audio subsystem and exit.
.SS "Modem options"
.TP
.BI \-m " mode_index"
Startup payload mode index (see
.BR \-l ).
Used for broadcast and idle/disconnected ARQ decode.
Default is 1 (DATAC3).
.TP
.BI \-s " mode_index"
Legacy alias for
.BR \-m .
.TP
.BI \-f " level"
FreeDV modem verbosity level, 0 to 3.
Default is 0.
.TP
.B \-l
List all available modulation/coding modes with their parameters and exit.
.TP
.B \-t
Test TX (transmit) mode.
.TP
.B \-r
Test RX (receive) mode.
.SS "Network options"
.TP
.BI \-p " port"
ARQ TCP base port.
The control port is
.IR port ,
and the data port is
.IR port +1.
Default is
.BR 8300 .
.TP
.BI \-b " port"
Broadcast TCP port.
Default is
.BR 8100 .
.SS "GUI options"
.TP
.B \-G
Enable UI communication (UDP status/spectrum/command sockets for
.BR mercury-qt ).
Off by default.
.TP
.BI \-u " ip"
UI IP address.
Default is
.BR 127.0.0.1 .
.TP
.BI \-U " port"
UI base port.
TX port is
.IR port ,
RX port is
.IR port +1,
spectrum port is
.IR port +2.
Default is
.BR 10000 .
.TP
.B \-W
Disable waterfall/spectrum data sent to the UI (saves CPU).
.SS "Radio control options"
.TP
.BI \-R " model"
Set Hamlib radio model (numeric ID).
Use
.B \-K
to list available models.
.TP
.BI \-A " address"
Set Hamlib radio device file or ip:port address (e.g.,
.IR /dev/ttyUSB0
or
.IR localhost:4532 ).
.TP
.B \-S
Use HERMES shared memory interface for PTT control instead of Hamlib.
Mutually exclusive with
.B \-R
and
.BR \-A .
Available only on Linux builds.
.TP
.B \-K
List Hamlib supported radio models and exit.
.SS "Logging options"
.TP
.BI \-L " path"
Write log to file (TIMING level and above).
In verbose mode, log level is DEBUG.
.TP
.B \-J
Use JSONL format for the log file (requires
.BR \-L ).
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose mode.
Enables debug-level logging.
.SS "System options"
.TP
.BI \-c " cpu"
Pin the process to CPU number
.IR cpu .
Use \-1 to disable CPU selection (default).
Linux only.
.TP
.B \-h
Print usage help and exit.
.SH TNC INTERFACE
Mercury provides a VARA-compatible TCP TNC interface for ARQ operations.
The control port accepts text commands terminated by a carriage return,
and sends asynchronous status responses.
The data port carries the raw byte stream.
.SS "Commands (control port)"
.TP
.BI "MYCALL " callsign
Set the local station callsign (up to 15 characters).
.TP
.BI "LISTEN " "ON|OFF"
Enable or disable listening for incoming connections.
.TP
.BI "PUBLIC " "ON|OFF"
Enable or disable public mode (accept connections from any station).
.TP
.BI "CONNECT " "mycall " destcall
Initiate an ARQ connection from
.I mycall
to
.IR destcall .
.TP
.B DISCONNECT
Disconnect the current ARQ session.
.TP
.BI "BW" bandwidth
Set the channel bandwidth in Hz.
Valid values:
.B 500
(narrow),
.B 2300
(full), or
.B 2750
(tactical).
Default is 2300.
.TP
.BI "RETRIES " count
Set the maximum number of retransmission attempts.
.TP
.B BUFFER
Query the number of bytes pending in the transmit buffer.
.TP
.B SN
Query the current signal-to-noise ratio.
.TP
.B BITRATE
Query the current bitrate.
.TP
.BI "CQFRAME " "callsign " bandwidth
Transmit a CQ broadcast frame.
.I bandwidth
accepts the same values as
.BR BW .
.TP
.B COMPRESSION ON|OFF
Accepted for VARA compatibility; no-op.
.TP
.B CHAT ON|OFF
.B CHAT ON
implies
.BR "LISTEN ON" ;
.B CHAT OFF
is a no-op.
Accepted for VARA compatibility.
.TP
.B P2P
Accepted for VARA compatibility; no-op.
.SS "Responses (control port)"
.TP
.B OK
Command accepted.
.TP
.B WRONG
Command rejected or malformed.
.TP
.BI "CONNECTED " "source " "dest " bandwidth
ARQ link established between
.I source
and
.IR dest .
.TP
.B DISCONNECTED
ARQ link terminated.
.TP
.B PENDING
Outgoing connection attempt in progress.
.TP
.B CANCELPENDING
Outgoing connection attempt cancelled.
.TP
.BI "BUFFER " bytes
Number of bytes remaining in the transmit buffer.
Sent periodically and in response to BUFFER queries.
.TP
.BI "SN " snr
Current signal-to-noise ratio in dB (e.g., \(lqSN 12.5\(rq).
.TP
.BI "BITRATE (" speed_level ") " bps " BPS"
Current bitrate in bits per second and the speed ladder level.
.TP
.BI "CQFRAME " callsign " " bandwidth
Received a CQ broadcast from
.IR callsign .
.SH FREEDV MODES
Mercury uses the following FreeDV OFDM waveforms:
.PP
.TS
l l l l.
Mode	Index	Usage	Notes
_
DATAC1	0	Payload	502 bytes/frame, highest throughput
DATAC3	1	Payload	118 bytes/frame, default startup mode
DATAC0	2	Payload	6 bytes/frame
DATAC4	3	Payload	46 bytes/frame, lowest SNR requirement
DATAC13	4	Control	6 bytes/frame, ARQ control channel
DATAC14	5	Control	1 byte/frame
FSK_LDPC	6	Payload	22 bytes/frame
.TE
.PP
In ARQ mode, DATAC13 is always used for the control channel.
The payload channel starts at DATAC4 and upgrades through DATAC3 to
DATAC1 as channel conditions permit.
The dual-decoder architecture runs control and payload decoders
simultaneously.
.SH DEFAULT PORTS
.PP
.TS
l l l.
Service	Port	Protocol
_
ARQ control	8300	TCP
ARQ data	8301	TCP
Broadcast	8100	TCP
UI TX	10000	UDP
UI RX	10001	UDP
UI spectrum	10002	UDP
.TE
.SH EXAMPLES
Start mercury with default settings (ALSA, DATAC3, port 8300):
.PP
.RS
.nf
mercury \-i plughw:1,0 \-o plughw:1,0
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start with verbose logging to a JSONL file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mercury \-i plughw:1,0 \-o plughw:1,0 \-v \-L /var/log/mercury.jsonl \-J
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start with Hamlib radio control (rigctld on localhost):
.PP
.RS
.nf
mercury \-i plughw:1,0 \-o plughw:1,0 \-R 2 \-A localhost:4532
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start with HERMES shared memory PTT control:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mercury \-i plughw:1,0 \-o plughw:1,0 \-S
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start with PulseAudio, narrow bandwidth, and GUI enabled:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mercury \-x pulse \-m 3 \-G
.fi
.RE
.PP
List available modulation modes:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mercury \-l
.fi
.RE
.PP
List available sound cards:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mercury \-z
.fi
.RE
.PP
List supported Hamlib radio models:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mercury \-K
.fi
.RE
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGINT\fR, \fBSIGTERM
Graceful shutdown.
Mercury releases audio devices, closes TCP connections, and shuts down
the radio control interface before exiting.
